      "citation_id": "[CITATION_1]",
      "span_text": "For primary SS, no international or American College of Rheumatology (ACR) classification set of criteria exists and as the time from a patient's first symptom to diagnosis is 7-9 years, it seems obvious that a new set of classification criteria is needed to add to the seven different sets of criteria produced during the past 25 years. A look at articles published in English within this field shows that the European criteria from 1993 or 1996 2 3 are the ones most commonly cited, while the Copenhagen criteria 4 are used in China and, seemingly, the ones most used world wide."
